title: Grand Canyon National Park - National Park Service audio recording - Canyon Wren 1
creator: National Park Service
description: Audio tracks of animal sounds - Canyon Wren at Grand Canyon National Park. Canyon Wrens are some of the most commonly seen birds in the Grand Canyon. Their most common call is a series of notes that follow a pattern of "tee-tee-tee-tee-tew-tew-tew-tew" as they descend in pitch.
